00:23:13.740 --> 00:23:17.670
give Joe the opportunity to
round up why we are here

00:23:17.670 --> 00:23:23.230
today, is our next long
term development.

00:23:23.230 --> 00:23:26.840
Nicholas has just been named
Chairman of a very interesting

00:23:26.840 --> 00:23:29.670
project which is the X-Prize
project that you guys are

00:23:29.670 --> 00:23:33.820
involved with, because of
this particular project.

00:23:33.820 --> 00:23:38.490
It just happened that we are
interested in children that

00:23:38.490 --> 00:23:42.220
had no opportunity whatsoever
to know how to read.

00:23:42.220 --> 00:23:46.070
When they are 30 kilometres away
from the nearest school.

00:23:46.070 --> 00:23:50.440
And where nobody in their
communities or villages know

00:23:50.440 --> 00:23:51.940
how to read.

00:23:51.940 --> 00:23:57.010
And we think that there are
between 60 million and 100

00:23:57.010 --> 00:23:59.830
million of these children
worldwide.

00:23:59.830 --> 00:24:02.850
So we went and looked around and
we found in Ethiopia this

00:24:02.850 --> 00:24:07.140
community in the crater of a
volcano up in the mountains of

00:24:07.140 --> 00:24:09.160
4,000 meters high up.

00:24:09.160 --> 00:24:13.250
And we distributed, together
with Sugata Mitra--

00:24:13.250 --> 00:24:15.950
which you already
know as well--

00:24:15.950 --> 00:24:18.600
on the Hole in the Wall
project in India.

00:24:18.600 --> 00:24:21.420
And together with this lady by
the name of Maryanne Wolf from

00:24:21.420 --> 00:24:25.400
Tufts University who dedicated
her life to study autism.

00:24:25.400 --> 00:24:29.920
And through that she started
to understand when mankind

00:24:29.920 --> 00:24:31.260
learned how to read.

00:24:31.260 --> 00:24:36.100
When you pass from a very
graphic description of the

00:24:36.100 --> 00:24:40.260
Egyptians' hieroglyphics to the
very abstract writing of

00:24:40.260 --> 00:24:43.020
cuneiform writing code
of the Assyrians.

00:24:43.020 --> 00:24:44.680
When that happened?

00:24:44.680 --> 00:24:47.450
She discovers and she explains
in her book.

00:24:47.450 --> 00:24:49.990
The size of the brain
increased in about a

00:24:49.990 --> 00:24:55.160
millennium or two from about
600 grams to 1,000 grams.

00:24:55.160 --> 00:24:59.360
So the brain had to create an
enormous amount of cells in

00:24:59.360 --> 00:25:02.510
order to be able to understand
the passage from a figurative

00:25:02.510 --> 00:25:04.690
environment to an abstract
environment.

00:25:04.690 --> 00:25:06.920
So together with these two
gentlemen, a lady and

00:25:06.920 --> 00:25:09.410
gentleman, we have launched
this project.

00:25:09.410 --> 00:25:10.130
And this is--

00:25:10.130 --> 00:25:12.180
unfortunately it's too
dark for this one--

00:25:12.180 --> 00:25:14.120
these are the villages
in Ethiopia.

00:25:14.120 --> 00:25:18.990
And we about eight months ago
started a project in two

00:25:18.990 --> 00:25:20.650
villages with 23 computers.

00:25:20.650 --> 00:25:23.890
These are Motorola laptops,
not computers but tablets.

00:25:23.890 --> 00:25:24.730
This is the environment.

00:25:24.730 --> 00:25:25.630
This is the type of village.

00:25:25.630 --> 00:25:27.650
There is no electricity,
no sign.

00:25:27.650 --> 00:25:30.820
The only words that we were able
to find were some of the

00:25:30.820 --> 00:25:32.680
clothes that had the
Adidas name.

00:25:32.680 --> 00:25:34.790
Or whatever type of description

00:25:34.790 --> 00:25:36.130
that came in the clothing.

00:25:36.130 --> 00:25:38.870
Nobody in the communities
learned how to read or write.

00:25:38.870 --> 00:25:40.610
They had never seen a sign.

00:25:40.610 --> 00:25:43.540
And the only thing that we
installed was a solar panel to

00:25:43.540 --> 00:25:44.850
charge the batteries that every

00:25:44.850 --> 00:25:46.950
night charged the computers.

00:25:46.950 --> 00:25:47.650
The tablets.

00:25:47.650 --> 00:25:49.530
And these are Motorola
tablets.

00:25:49.530 --> 00:25:54.590
And we gave the boxes
to the children.

00:25:54.590 --> 00:25:59.780
And 10 minutes later everybody
has un-boxed the tablets.

00:25:59.780 --> 00:26:04.070
15 minutes later on they
knew how to turn it on.

00:26:04.070 --> 00:26:07.910
Two days later on they were
already exploring.

00:26:07.910 --> 00:26:13.130
And the whole thing was so
incredible that even a month

00:26:13.130 --> 00:26:19.950
and a half later on we have not
put the video camera to

00:26:19.950 --> 00:26:22.080
use because we were afraid that
they were going to start

00:26:22.080 --> 00:26:23.910
streaming video.

00:26:23.910 --> 00:26:28.110
And they hacked the tablet and
they put the camera to work.

00:26:28.110 --> 00:26:31.130
I mean, nobody knew
how to do it.

00:26:31.130 --> 00:26:33.390
And that's when the tipping
point came to us.

00:26:33.390 --> 00:26:35.600
This is something again
transformational.

00:26:35.600 --> 00:26:37.750
And this is something that
we should look around.

00:26:37.750 --> 00:26:40.066
And that's when Nicholas about a
month ago came and talked to

00:26:40.066 --> 00:26:43.430
Larry and Sergey.

00:26:43.430 --> 00:26:46.890
And in that group together
with other companies they

00:26:46.890 --> 00:26:48.050
created the X-Prize.

00:26:48.050 --> 00:26:51.170
And they are now putting $10
million to develop a project

00:26:51.170 --> 00:26:54.300
in the next two years of the
most innovative way of

00:26:54.300 --> 00:26:57.010
teaching or learning
how to read.

00:26:57.010 --> 00:27:00.910
Because if you learn
how to read, then

00:27:00.910 --> 00:27:02.630
you read how to learn.

00:27:02.630 --> 00:27:06.040
There's a tipping point about
seven or eight years of age in

00:27:06.040 --> 00:27:09.330
which, if you have learned how
to read, then you can use that

00:27:09.330 --> 00:27:12.820
reading expertise into
reading how to learn.

00:27:12.820 --> 00:27:14.570
And that's where we
are interested in.

00:27:14.570 --> 00:27:17.290
And that's the frontier in
which we want to advance.

00:27:17.290 --> 00:27:20.460
And this is the type of
environments that you can see.

00:27:20.460 --> 00:27:22.600
Together they are working.

