This kid is looking at
this other kid work.

00:27:31.960 --> 00:27:34.380
This kid is looking
at this other one.

00:27:34.380 --> 00:27:35.940
Then you have one that
is sort of the

00:27:35.940 --> 00:27:38.550
supervisor or the teacher.

00:27:38.550 --> 00:27:41.890
And this is complete environment
self-created by

00:27:41.890 --> 00:27:45.980
them, in terms of how a complete
village can really

00:27:45.980 --> 00:27:49.220
take into their own hands,
something that until then was

00:27:49.220 --> 00:27:51.880
absolutely not existent.

00:27:51.880 --> 00:27:56.370
So a few weeks later on if you
could see, they were already

00:27:56.370 --> 00:27:57.100
doing the alphabet.

00:27:57.100 --> 00:27:59.660
And they were already writing
in the floor.

00:27:59.660 --> 00:28:00.140
They learned.

00:28:00.140 --> 00:28:04.230
They were already singing the
alphabet, A-B-C-D-E-F. And

00:28:04.230 --> 00:28:09.620
they are now really giving us
the first glimpse that indeed

00:28:09.620 --> 00:28:12.990
a child could really
learn how to read.

00:28:12.990 --> 00:28:17.300
And if we prove that in the
next couple of years, this

00:28:17.300 --> 00:28:22.140
will be as transformational
as the entire element from

00:28:22.140 --> 00:28:24.760
Gutenberg printing stage.

00:28:24.760 --> 00:28:26.870
This could be a transformational
element.

00:28:26.870 --> 00:28:29.530
Because until now we have been
told that you need a teacher

00:28:29.530 --> 00:28:31.770
to tell you how to read.

